# Todo App - Frontend

React application built with Vite and React Router DOM.

## Tech Stack

- **Framework:** React 18
- **Build Tool:** Vite
- **Routing:** React Router DOM v6
- **HTTP Client:** Axios

## Setup & Run

```bash
npm install
npm run dev       # development server on http://localhost:5173
npm run build     # production build
```

> Make sure the backend is running on port 5000 before starting the frontend.

---

## Pages

### 1. Todo List Page — `/`

The main page of the application.

**Features:**
- View all todos in a clean card layout
- Add new todos using the inline form
- Mark todos as complete or incomplete with a checkbox
- Delete todos (with confirmation prompt)
- Click View to go to the detail page
- Search todos by title in real time
- Filter by status: All / Active / Done
- Filter by priority: All / Low / Medium / High
- Stats bar showing total, pending, and completed counts
- Color-coded priority indicators (green / orange / red)
- Overdue date warning shown in red

### 2. Todo Detail Page — `/todo?id=<uuid>`

Accessed by clicking the View button on any todo card.

**Features:**
- Displays full todo information
- Shows status badge (Completed / Pending)
- Shows priority badge with color
- Shows formatted due date
- Shows created and last updated timestamps
- Shows full description
- Edit mode — click Edit Todo to modify title, description, priority, due date, and completion status
- Save or Cancel changes
- Success message shown after saving
- Back button to return to the list

---

## Components

| Component | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| `TodoList.jsx` | Main page with list, filters, and search |
| `TodoDetail.jsx` | Detail and edit page for a single todo |
| `TodoItem.jsx` | Individual todo card component |
| `AddTodo.jsx` | Form to create a new todo |
| `FilterBar.jsx` | Status and priority filter controls |
| `todoApi.js` | Axios API helper functions |

---

## Routing

React Router DOM is used for multi-page navigation (not SPA). Each route is a distinct page:

| Route | Page |
|-------|------|
| `/` | Todo list page |
| `/todo?id=<uuid>` | Single todo detail page |

The `id` is passed as a **URL query parameter** and read with `useSearchParams()`.
